Dear Christopher,

Following up on the issue, please proceed with the steps below and share the results with us:

  1.  Download the new build <https://releases.netwrix.com/products/pingcastle/3.3/pingcastle-standard-3.3.0.9.zip>
  2.  Run the Azure AD scan again, this time using logging options enabled.
  3.  Share the scan results and logs for further analysis.

Additionally, could you confirm whether the PowerShell MSOnline module is restricted in any way on your side?

Lastly, I’d like to inform you that we will be migrating to Microsoft Graph as soon as we complete the work for the current release.

Looking forward to your update. Let me know if you need any assistance.

Best regards,

Hi Chris,

I wanted to provide you with some additional insight as to where we’re at with this effort.  Ultimately the team is working on migrating the bad calls from the provisioningAPI (the MSOnline)  to the graph API for the deprecation on March 30th. We have a developer currently assigned to and working on this.  If we have an available beta build before the GA release we will provide it once ready.  There is some suspicion there is something on the Microsoft side blocking us somewhere as we have been unable to reproduce the behavior.

Hopefully this provides you some clarity on where things stand.  If you have any additional questions please let us know.

Best regards,

Taylor
